{
  "texts": [
    "The initial step in SBDD is to identify drug targets and obtain their three-dimensional structure, which can be experimentally measured or computationally predicted using methods like homology modeling [13].",
    "Molecular dockingOnce the 3D structure of proteins is obtained, the subsequent step involves exploring atomic-level interactions between macromolecular structures and small molecules [38].",
    "The most well-known SBDD technique in this process is molecular docking.",
    "Docking methods typically consist of two components: the search algorithm and the scoring scheme [39,40].",
    "The search algorithm is responsible for sampling suitable conformations from high-dimensional spaces, while the scoring scheme is employed to evaluate interaction energies and rank different candidate dockings [41,42]."
  ]
}